node.text:
My Nanu (maternal grandmother) passed away on November 21. She was the matriarch of our family, extending multiple generations. In this episode of Our Way Home, we hope to honor her… our family’s North Star. ⁣
⁣
Please pray for my Nanu's peaceful rest & for strength for my mother and family back home. ⁣
⁣
Inna lillahi wa inna ilayhi raji'un 💕

TW: Rape, Violence & Sexual Assault • I just need 2.5 minutes of your time. Please listen, share and stand with Bangladesh. ⁣
⁣
Protestors have gathered over the last several days in Bangladesh after a series of horrific and brutal gang rapes and attacks. We must stand with the protestors in Bangladesh who are fighting for justice and reform. We must spread awareness and speak up, as their voices are being silenced by a system that refuses to change and protect women. ⁣
⁣
It is well overdue for a massive shift in how rape culture is addressed in Bangladesh, how attackers are punished and how survivors are treated. I urge you to watch the full video, share it and other articles/content surrounding this issue and speak up for Bangladesh, a country that is continually forgotten and ignored in times of injustice and despair. ⁣
⁣
I believe in the power of our unified voices. I believe that together we can cultivate a stronger and more just Bangladesh. ⁣
⁣
I am proud of every single protestor who has continued to stand up against injustice with peace and passion at the forefront. I admire every single one of you. I am here for you. I stand with you. And hopefully the world will join us too. 🤍⁣
⁣
The information and stats shared in this video are sourced from the following resources below:  @taniarashid @aljazeeraenglish amnesty.org @asianuktv @dhakatribune @dailystar_bd

node.text:
I’m currently wrapped in a chunky knit blanket with a piercing headache but in my mind I’m celebrating Eid with @itssethmar and the entire Noor family. 🥺🥰 ⁣
⁣
Hoping to feel more like myself by the evening for Eid dinner with everyone. What is your favorite way to celebrate holidays with your family?⁣
⁣
I love when Mama Noor makes delicious food and we all play charades with the grandkids and Seth whisks off with my brothers for some bro time, while checking on my Baba’s every need in between and making sure to reheat his chai. 🥺⁣
⁣
In honor of today, I’m giving away a few @Target electronic gift cards to some commenters and will announce the winners on stories later today. ⁣
⁣
Eid Mubarak, friends!! 🌙✨

node.text:
As I approach my 30th birthday, I’m thinking about how much has changed around me and within me. My prayer for 30 is that this journey of self-exploration only becomes stronger and that I welcome change in all areas of life - because nothing changes if nothing changes.🌿⁣
⁣
If anyone is holding you to who you were and not allowing you the space to grow into who you want to be, let me be the first to tell you: I am so proud of you for exploring and growing. Keep blooming, friend.🌻

node.text:
Over the weekend as I managed my calendar for next week, my heart dropped as I saw a series of ultrasound and baby related appointments slated for next week that I forgot to remove since our loss. After removing each one by one, with a broken heart, I looked at @itssethmar and he gave me a giant hug, smiled and said “Soon they’ll be back on our calendar.” 🤍 ⁣
⁣
I share this for every one of you who are reminded in little ways of your loss throughout your day... ⁣
⁣
Soon the blessing of motherhood will be placed on our calendar - maybe when we least expect it. ✨
